Yohan Goutt Goncalves represents Timor-Leste in the alpine skiing here at the Beijing 2022 Winter Olympic Games, his third time at the Olympics. At Sochi 2014, he became the first athlete to represent the small island nation at the Winter Games. Fun fact: Timor Leste, located between Indonesia and Australia, is a tropical country where it never snows. CGTN reporter Cen Ziyuan talks to Goncalves about his trip to Beijing. (Cover: Yohan Goutt Goncalves talks with CGTN. /courtesy of Goncalves)